## Steps

### step 1
id: open-patient
instruction: Open a patient record using the find-patient flow or by clicking a patient from the Patients list.
success_criteria: You are on the patient detail page. The Overview tab is showing demographics and summary tiles.
anchor: "patient detail"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Use the find-patient flow first to locate the patient.

### step 2
id: click-encounters-tab
instruction: Click the "Encounters" tab to see the patient's complete visit history.
success_criteria: The Encounters tab is active. A chronological timeline of visits is displayed, newest first. Each card shows date of service, billed amount, status badge, provider, payer, and procedure codes. Red highlighting means a denial exists.
anchor: "Encounters"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The Encounters tab is one of the tabs at the top of the patient detail page.

### step 3
id: click-into-encounter
instruction: Click on any encounter card to open its full detail page to manage it.
success_criteria: You are on the encounter detail page for the selected visit.
anchor: "encounter card"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click on any encounter card.

## Completion Message
you can see this patient's complete billing history. red encounters have denials that need attention. click into any one to manage it.

